      "source": [
        "## Architecture Summary\n",
        "\n",
        "### Model: PBRNet (Encoder–Decoder)\n",
        "- **Encoder**: 5-layer CNN with residual blocks → 512-dim bottleneck\n",
        "- **Texture Decoders**: Per-map decoders from 256-dim latent → 128×128 textures\n",
        "- **Scalar Head**: FC layers for transmission, IOR, anisotropy, etc.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Renderer: Cook-Torrance PBR\n",
        "- **GGX** normal distribution function\n",
        "- **Smith-GGX** geometry / self-shadowing\n",
        "- **Schlick Fresnel** approximation\n",
        "- **Direct light** with configurable direction, color, intensity\n",
        "- **HDR environment** (procedural sky + sun + ground bounce)\n",
        "- **Reinhard tonemapping**\n",
        "\n",
        "### 16 PBR Output Parameters\n",
        "| Texture Maps | Scalars |\n",
        "|---|---|\n",
        "| Base Color (RGB) | Transmission |\n",
        "| Metallic (Gray) | IOR |\n",
        "| Roughness (Gray) | Anisotropy |\n",
        "| Specular (RGB) | Anisotropic Rotation |\n",
        "| Glossiness (Gray) | Specular Tint |\n",
        "| Normal Map (XYZ) | |\n",
        "| Ambient Occlusion (Gray) | |\n",
        "| Height / Displacement (Gray) | |\n",
        "| Opacity (Gray) | |\n",
        "| Emissive (RGB) | |\n",
        "| Subsurface Scattering (RGB) | |\n",
        "\n",
        "### Next Steps\n",
        "1. Load real HDR environment maps (.hdr/.exr) for image-based lighting\n",
        "2. Replace sphere with arbitrary meshes via PyTorch3D\n",
        "3. Add perceptual loss (LPIPS) alongside MSE\n",
        "4. Scale texture output resolution from 128×128 to 512×512\n",
        "5. Add multi-light training with randomized light positions"
      ]
    }
